Dear Administrative Court Office,

=20

Further to my email of 19 January 2026, I write to confirm that the Claiman=
t=E2=80=99s Reply to the Defendants=E2=80=99 Summary Grounds of Resistance is in active =
preparation and will be filed shortly.

=20

The Reply relies on a structured evidential dataset derived from contempora=
neous correspondence, which is currently being finalised.

=20

In those circumstances, I respectfully request that permission is not deter=
mined for a period of five business days from today, to allow the Reply to b=
e completed and filed.

=20

I would be grateful if this request could be placed on the court file.

=20

Yours faithfully,

=20

Nadia Zahmoul

Claimant (Litigant in Person)

